rule.name: Query clauses spanning multiple lines should begin on own line

rule.name: Opening parenthesis or bracket should be on declaration line
rule.description:

rule.name: Closing parenthesis should be on line of last parameter
rule.description:
The closing parenthesis or bracket in a call to or declaration of a C# method/indexer/attribute/array/constructor/delegate is not placed on the same line as the last parameter.

rule.description:

rule.name: Comma should be on the same line as previous parameter
rule.description:
A comma between two parameters in a call to a C# method or indexer, or in the declaration of a method or indexer, is not placed on the same line as the previous parameter.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Parameter list should follow declaration
rule.description:
The start of the parameter list for a method/constructor/indexer/array/operator call or declaration does not begin on the same line as the opening bracket, or on the line after the opening bracket.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Parameter should follow comma
rule.description:
A parameter within a C# method or indexer call or declaration does not begin on the same line as the previous parameter, or on the next line.

rule.name: Split parameters should start on line after declaration
rule.description:

rule.name: Parameters should be on same line or separate lines

rule.name: Parameter should not span multiple lines
rule.description:
A parameter to a C# method/indexer/attribute/array, other than the first parameter, spans across multiple lines. If the parameter is short, place the entire parameter on a single line. Otherwise, save the contents of the parameter in a temporary variable and pass the temporary variable as a parameter.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Do not use default value type constructor
rule.description:
When creating a new instance of a value type T, the syntax 'default(T)' is functionally equivalent to the syntax 'new T()'. To avoid confusion regarding the behavior of the resulting instance, the first form is preferred.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Use lambda syntax
rule.description:
Lambda expressions are more succinct and easier to read than anonymous methods, so they should are preferred whenever the two are functionally equivalent.

rule.name: Use readable conditions
rule.description:
When a comparison is made between a variable and a literal, the variable should be placed on the left-hand-side to maximize readability.

rule.name: Do not combine fields
rule.description:
Each field should be declared on its own line, in order to clearly see each field of a type and allow for proper documentation of the behavior of each field.

rule.name: Do not combine attributes

The tags within the Xml header documentation for a generic C# element do not match the generic type parameters on the element.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Generic type parameter documentation should declare parameter name
rule.description:
A tag within the XML header documentation for a generic C# element is missing a name attribute, or contains an empty name attribute.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Generic type parameter documentation should have text
rule.description:
A tag within the Xml header documentation for a generic C# element is empty.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Property summary documentation should match accessors
rule.description:
The documentation text within a C# propertys tag does not match the accessors within the property.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Property summary documentation should omit accessor with restricted access
rule.description:
The documentation text within a C# propertys tag takes into account all of the accessors within the property, but one of the accessors has limited access.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Elements should be documented
rule.description:
A C# code element is missing a documentation header.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Partial elements should be documented
rule.description:
A C# partial element is missing a documentation header.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Enumeration items should be documented
rule.description:
An item within a C# enumeration is missing an Xml documentation header.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Documentation should contain valid XML
rule.description:
The XML within a C# elements document header is badly formed.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element documentation should have summary
rule.description:
The XML header documentation for a C# element is missing a tag.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Partial element documentation should have summary
rule.description:
The or tag within the documentation header for a C# code element is missing or empty.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element documentation should have summary text
rule.description:
The tag within the documentation header for a C# code element is empty.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Partial element documentation should have summary text
rule.description:
The or tag within the documentation header for a C# code element is empty.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element documentation should not have default summary
rule.description:
The tag within an element's XML header documentation contains the default text generated by Visual Studio during the creation of the element.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Property documentation should have value
rule.description:
The XML header documentation for a C# property does not contain a tag.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Property documentation should have value text
rule.description:
The XML header documentation for a C# property contains an empty tag.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element parameters should be documented
rule.description:
A C# method, constructor, delegate or indexer element is missing documentation for one or more of its parameters.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element parameter documentation should match element parameters
rule.description:
The documentation describing the parameters to a C# method, constructor, delegate or indexer element does not match the actual parameters on the element.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element parameter documentation should declare parameter name
rule.description:
A tag within a C# element's documentation header is missing a name attribute containing the name of the parameter.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element parameter documentation should have text
rule.description:
A tag within a C# element's documentation header is empty.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element return value should be documented
rule.description:
A C# element is missing documentation for its return value.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element return value documentation should have text
rule.description:
The tag within a C# element's documentation header is empty.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Void return value should not be documented
rule.description:
A C# code element does not contain a return value, or returns void, but the documentation header for the element contains a tag.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Generic type parameters should be documented
rule.description:
A generic C# element is missing documentation for one or more of its generic type parameters.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Generic type parameters should be documented partial class
rule.description:
A generic, partial C# element is missing documentation for one or more of its generic type parameters, and the documentation for the element contains a tag.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Element documentation should not be copied and pasted
rule.description:
The Xml documentation for a C# element contains two or more identical entries, indicating that the documentation has been copied and pasted. This can sometimes indicate invalid or poorly written documentation.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Single-line comments should not use documentation style slashes
rule.description:
The C# code contains a single-line comment which begins with three forward slashes in a row.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Documentation text should not be empty
rule.description:
The XML header documentation for a C# code element contains an empty tag.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Documentation text should begin with a capital letter
rule.description:
A section of the XML header documentation for a C# element does not begin with a capital letter.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Documentation text should end with a period
rule.description:
A section of the XML header documentation for a C# element does not end with a period.
More Details For more information visit the rule's help page.

rule.name: Documentation text should contain whitespace
rule.description:
A section of the XML header documentation for a C# element does not contain any whitespace between words.

rule.name: Documentation should meet character percentage

rule.name: Documentation text should meet minimum character length

rule.name: Constructor summary documentation should begin with standard text

rule.name: Destructor summary documentation should begin with standard text

rule.name: Documentation headers should not contain blank lines

rule.name: Included documentation file does not exist

An included XML documentation file does not exist.

rule.name: Include node does not contain valid file and path

rule.name: inheritdoc should be used with inheriting class
rule.description:
has been used on an element that doesn't inherit from a base class or implement an interface.

rule.name: File name should match first type name

The file name of a C# code file does not match the first type declared in the file.

rule.name: Element documentation should be spelled correctly

The element documentation for the element contains one or more spelling mistakes or unrecognized words.

rule.name: Do not use placeholder elements

The element documentation contains a element.
